Believing that a foreign writer can be born in you increases first the intensity, then the frequency, and finally the pleasure of reading's impact on you. You no longer look at the author from across an abyss of otherness. His difficulties are not road bumps on the way toward `Nature Realized.' No, no, his difficulties are your own, and that pain, those tears, hover close as ever. He speaks to you, not about you.
